Program: The History Hour
Title: The Awakenings
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csypzn
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 17 Dec 2019
An extraordinary medical experiment that brought the catatonic back to life; an IRA siege in the 70s; the killing of a young immigrant in New York that sparked mass protests; an attack on the Indian parliament in 2001, and the fight to build the Louvre's iconic pyramid in Paris. Picture: Dr Concetta Tomaino (center) with Dr Oliver Sacks (right) and patient (left) (Credit: the American Music Therapy Association) Show less